Feature: Apply without sync # scenarios/bad_practices/apply_without_sync.feature:2
  anklume must detect when the user skips the generate step and
  provides clear guidance to run "make sync" first.
  Feature: Apply without sync  # scenarios/bad_practices/apply_without_sync.feature:2

  Scenario: No inventory files exist              # scenarios/bad_practices/apply_without_sync.feature:9
    Given a clean sandbox environment             # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml exists but no inventory files # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:27
    When I run "make apply" and it may fail       # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:40
    Then exit code is non-zero                    # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:55

  Scenario: Stale inventory missing new domain          # scenarios/bad_practices/apply_without_sync.feature:14
    Given a clean sandbox environment                   # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml from "student-sysadmin"             # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:16
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml"  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                 # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    When I add a domain "new-domain" to infra.yml       # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:60
    Then file "inventory/new-domain.yml" does not exist # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:103
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml"  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                 # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    And file "inventory/new-domain.yml" exists          # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:97

Feature: CLI wrong dependency order # scenarios/bad_practices/cli_wrong_dependency_order.feature:1
  Running commands out of their dependency order leads to errors.
  The resource flow model enforces: producer must run before consumer.
  Feature: CLI wrong dependency order  # scenarios/bad_practices/cli_wrong_dependency_order.feature:1

  Scenario: apply without sync fails              # scenarios/bad_practices/cli_wrong_dependency_order.feature:8
    Given a clean sandbox environment             # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml exists but no inventory files # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:27
    When I run "make apply" and it may fail       # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:40
    Then exit code is non-zero                    # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:55

  Scenario: lint without sync fails                                   # scenarios/bad_practices/cli_wrong_dependency_order.feature:13
    Given a clean sandbox environment                                 # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given "yamllint" is available                                     # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    And infra.yml from "student-sysadmin"                             # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:16
    And no generated files exist                                      # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:51
    When I run "yamllint -c .yamllint.yml inventory/" and it may fail # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:40
    Then exit code is non-zero                                        # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:55

  Scenario: Sync with invalid infra.yml fails gracefully               # scenarios/bad_practices/cli_wrong_dependency_order.feature:20
    Given a clean sandbox environment                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml with invalid trust_level "super-trusted"           # scenarios/steps/validation_steps.py:205
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml" and it may fail # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:40
    Then exit code is non-zero                                         # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:55
    And output contains "trust_level"                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:63

Feature: Delete protected instance # scenarios/bad_practices/delete_protected_instance.feature:2
  The flush command requires confirmation to prevent accidental destruction.
  On production hosts (absolute_level=0), it requires --force explicitly.
  Feature: Delete protected instance  # scenarios/bad_practices/delete_protected_instance.feature:2

  Scenario: Flush without --force asks for confirmation and aborts  # scenarios/bad_practices/delete_protected_instance.feature:10
    Given a clean sandbox environment                               # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    And Incus daemon is available                                   # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:27
    When I run "scripts/flush.sh" and it may fail                   # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:40
    Then output contains "anklume Flush"                            # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:63

  Scenario: Flush with --force destroys infrastructure  # scenarios/bad_practices/delete_protected_instance.feature:14
    Given a clean sandbox environment                   # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    And Incus daemon is available                       # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:27
    When I run "scripts/flush.sh --force"               # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                 # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    And output contains "Flush complete"                # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:63

Feature: Duplicate IPs in infra.yml # scenarios/bad_practices/duplicate_ips.feature:2
  The PSOT generator must reject configurations with duplicate IPs
  across domains and provide a clear error message.
  Feature: Duplicate IPs in infra.yml  # scenarios/bad_practices/duplicate_ips.feature:2

  Scenario: Two machines share the same IP                             # scenarios/bad_practices/duplicate_ips.feature:9
    Given a clean sandbox environment                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml with two machines sharing "10.100.200.10"          # scenarios/steps/validation_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml" and it may fail # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:40
    Then exit code is non-zero                                         # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:55
    And output contains "already used"                                 # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:63
    And file "inventory/test-a.yml" does not exist                     # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:103

Feature: Edit managed sections # scenarios/bad_practices/edit_managed_sections.feature:2
  Content inside managed sections is overwritten by "make sync".
  Users must be warned that their changes will be lost.
  Feature: Edit managed sections  # scenarios/bad_practices/edit_managed_sections.feature:2

  Scenario: Managed section content is overwritten by sync           # scenarios/bad_practices/edit_managed_sections.feature:9
    Given a clean sandbox environment                                # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml from "student-sysadmin"                          # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:16
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml"               # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                              # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    When I edit the managed section in "group_vars/anklume.yml"      # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:76
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml"               # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                              # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    And the managed section in "group_vars/anklume.yml" is unchanged # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:109

Feature: Forget nftables-deploy after adding domain # scenarios/bad_practices/forget_nftables_deploy.feature:2
  After adding a new domain and running make apply, the user must
  regenerate and deploy nftables rules. Without this step, the new
  domain's network is not isolated.
  Feature: Forget nftables-deploy after adding domain  # scenarios/bad_practices/forget_nftables_deploy.feature:2

  Scenario: New domain added without nftables update  # scenarios/bad_practices/forget_nftables_deploy.feature:10
    Given a clean sandbox environment                 # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml from "student-sysadmin"           # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:16
    When I add a domain "new-unsecured" to infra.yml  # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:60
    And I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                               # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    And inventory files exist for all domains         # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:89
    And file "inventory/new-unsecured.yml" exists     # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:97

  Scenario: Nftables generation produces rules for all domains                   # scenarios/bad_practices/forget_nftables_deploy.feature:18
    Given a clean sandbox environment                                            # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml from "pro-workstation"                                       # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:16
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml"                           # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                          # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml --dry-run" and it may fail # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:40
    Then exit code is 0                                                          # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

Feature: Invalid boot and snapshot configuration # scenarios/bad_practices/invalid_boot_config.feature:2
  The generator validates boot_autostart, boot_priority,
  snapshots_schedule, and snapshots_expiry fields.
  Feature: Invalid boot and snapshot configuration  # scenarios/bad_practices/invalid_boot_config.feature:2

  Scenario: Generator rejects invalid cron schedule                    # scenarios/bad_practices/invalid_boot_config.feature:9
    Given a clean sandbox environment                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml with invalid snapshots_schedule "not-a-cron"       # scenarios/steps/validation_steps.py:39
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml" and it may fail # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:40
    Then exit code is non-zero                                         # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:55
    And output contains "snapshots_schedule"                           # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:63

  Scenario: Generator rejects invalid expiry format                    # scenarios/bad_practices/invalid_boot_config.feature:15
    Given a clean sandbox environment                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml with invalid snapshots_expiry "forever"            # scenarios/steps/validation_steps.py:63
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml" and it may fail # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:40
    Then exit code is non-zero                                         # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:55
    And output contains "snapshots_expiry"                             # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:63

  Scenario: Generator rejects boot_priority out of range               # scenarios/bad_practices/invalid_boot_config.feature:21
    Given a clean sandbox environment                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml with boot_priority 999                             # scenarios/steps/validation_steps.py:87
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml" and it may fail # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:40
    Then exit code is non-zero                                         # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:55
    And output contains "boot_priority"                                # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:63

