@requires.generator
Feature: CLI dependency chain # scenarios/best_practices/cli_dependency_chain.feature:2
  Commands must be run in prerequisite order. The resource flow
  model (_cli_deps.yml) defines which commands produce and consume
  each resource. Running a consumer before its producer fails.
  @requires.generator
  Feature: CLI dependency chain  # scenarios/best_practices/cli_dependency_chain.feature:2

  Scenario: sync before apply                          # scenarios/best_practices/cli_dependency_chain.feature:10
    Given a clean sandbox environment                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml from "student-sysadmin"            # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:16
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    And inventory files exist for all domains          # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:89

  Scenario: Lint passes after sync                                                           # scenarios/best_practices/cli_dependency_chain.feature:16
    Given a clean sandbox environment                                                        # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given "yamllint" is available                                                            # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    And infra.yml from "student-sysadmin"                                                    # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:16
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml"                                       # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                      # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    When I run "yamllint -c .yamllint.yml inventory/ group_vars/ host_vars/" and it may fail # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:40
    Then exit code is 0                                                                      # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: Full bootstrap chain with pro-workstation  # scenarios/best_practices/cli_dependency_chain.feature:24
    Given a clean sandbox environment                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:19
    Given infra.yml from "pro-workstation"             # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:16
    When I run "python3 scripts/generate.py infra.yml" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    And inventory files exist for all domains          # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:89
    And generated host_vars contain valid IPs          # scenarios/steps/sync_steps.py:119

  Scenario: Full bootstrap chain with ai-tools         # scenarios/best_practices/cli_dependency_chain.feature:31
