    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                                                                    # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'import yaml; from pathlib import Path; fr=yaml.safe_load(Path("i18n/fr.yml").read_text()); assert len(fr)>10, "Only %d translations" % len(fr); print("fr.yml: %d entries" % len(fr))'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                                                                             # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: Mode persistence file location is documented                                                                                               # scenarios/generated/cli_modes.feature:10
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                       # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from pathlib import Path; spec=Path("docs/SPEC.md").read_text(); assert "~/.anklume/mode" in spec; print("mode path ok")'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    And output contains "mode path ok"                                                                                                                 # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:63

  Scenario: CLI modes are user, student, dev                                                                                                                                                            # scenarios/generated/cli_modes.feature:17
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                                                        # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'modes=["user","student","dev"]; from pathlib import Path; spec=Path("docs/SPEC.md").read_text(); ok=[m for m in modes if m in spec]; assert len(ok)==3; print("modes ok")'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                                                                 # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46
    And output contains "modes ok"                                                                                                                                                                      # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:63

