@pty_required @requires.pty_module
Feature: PTY manager # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:2
  Manages pseudo-terminal sessions that back the xterm.js WebSocket
  connections. Handles session creation, lifecycle, cleanup, and limits.
  Scenario: PTY session creates valid process                                                                                                                   # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:8
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession; s = PtySession(cmd=["/bin/echo","hi"]); assert s.fd >= 0 and s.pid > 0; s.close()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                         # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY session defaults to bash                                                                                                 # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:13
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                         # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession; s = PtySession(); assert s.cmd == ["/bin/bash"]; s.close()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY session accepts custom command                                                                                                          # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:18
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                        # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession; s = PtySession(cmd=["/bin/cat"]); assert s.cmd == ["/bin/cat"]; s.close()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                 # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY session accepts custom dimensions                                                                                                                 # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:23
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession; s = PtySession(cols=120, rows=40); assert s.cols == 120 and s.rows == 40; s.close()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                           # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY session resize updates dimensions                                                                                                                                    # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:28
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                                     # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession; s = PtySession(cmd=["/bin/bash"]); s.resize(200, 50); assert s.cols == 200 and s.rows == 50; s.close()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                                              # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY session write updates last_activity                                                                                                                                                                      # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:33
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                                                                         # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'import time; from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession; s = PtySession(cmd=["/bin/cat"]); t = s.last_activity; time.sleep(0.05); s.write(b"x"); assert s.last_activity > t; s.close()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                                                                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY session close cleans up fd and pid                                                                                                           # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:38
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                             # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession; s = PtySession(cmd=["/bin/bash"]); s.close(); assert s.fd == -1 and s.pid == 0'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                      # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY session double close is safe                                                                                              # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:43
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                          # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession; s = PtySession(cmd=["/bin/echo","x"]); s.close(); s.close()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                   # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY session alive is true for running process                                                                                          # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:48
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                   # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession; s = PtySession(cmd=["/bin/bash"]); assert s.alive is True; s.close()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                            # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY session alive is false after close                                                                                                  # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:53
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                    # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession; s = PtySession(cmd=["/bin/bash"]); s.close(); assert s.alive is False'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                             # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY session alive is false for exited process                                                                                                                                        # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:58
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                                                 # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'import time; from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession; s = PtySession(cmd=["/bin/true"]); time.sleep(0.2); alive = s.alive; s.close(); assert alive is False'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                                                          # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY manager enforces max sessions                                                                                                                                                                                                     # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:65
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                                                                                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtyManager; m = PtyManager(max_sessions=1); m.create("a"); failed = False; exec("try:\n m.create(chr(98))\nexcept RuntimeError:\n failed = True"); m.close_all(); assert failed'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                                                                                                           # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY manager create and get                                                                                                                   # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:70
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                         # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtyManager; m = PtyManager(); s = m.create("t"); assert m.get("t") is s; m.close_all()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY manager close removes session                                                                                                          # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:75
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                       # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtyManager; m = PtyManager(); m.create("t"); m.close("t"); assert m.get("t") is None'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY manager close nonexistent is safe                                                               # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:80
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtyManager; m = PtyManager(); m.close("nope")'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                         # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY manager close_all empties sessions                                                                                                                                     # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:85
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                                       # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtyManager; m = PtyManager(max_sessions=4); m.create("a"); m.create("b"); m.close_all(); assert len(m.sessions) == 0'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                                                # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY manager recreate same sid replaces session                                                                                                                                                        # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:90
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                                                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtyManager; m = PtyManager(max_sessions=2); s1 = m.create("x"); s2 = m.create("x"); assert s1 is not s2 and len(m.sessions) == 1; m.close_all()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                                                                           # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY manager idle cleanup removes timed-out sessions                                                                                                                                                                                                # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:95
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                                                                                                               # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'import time; from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtyManager; m = PtyManager(max_sessions=4, idle_timeout=0); m.create("old", cmd=["/bin/bash"]); time.sleep(0.05); m._cleanup_idle(); assert len(m.sessions) == 0; m.close_all()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY manager cleans up dead processes                                                                                                                                                                                                                  # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:100
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'import time; from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtyManager; m = PtyManager(max_sessions=4, idle_timeout=3600); m.create("dead", cmd=["/bin/true"]); time.sleep(0.2); m._cleanup_idle(); assert len(m.sessions) == 0; m.close_all()'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY manager get nonexistent returns None                                                                         # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:105
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                             # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtyManager; m = PtyManager(); assert m.get("nope") is None'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                      # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

  Scenario: PTY blocking read returns None on closed fd                                                                                                                                                           # scenarios/learn/pty_manager.feature:110
    Given "python3" is available                                                                                                                                                                                  # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:12
    When I run "python3 -c 'import time; from scripts.web.pty_manager import PtySession, PtyManager; s = PtySession(cmd=["/bin/true"]); time.sleep(0.2); s.close(); assert PtyManager._blocking_read(s) is None'" # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:34
    Then exit code is 0                                                                                                                                                                                           # scenarios/steps/common_steps.py:46

